      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-top: 5px;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .d5 {
      border-color: #e8611a55;
    }

    .d5 .dnum,
    .d5 .dlabel {
      color: var(--accent1);
    }

    .d4 {
      border-color: #f59e0b55;
    }

    .d4 .dnum,
    .d4 .dlabel {
      color: #f59e0b;
    }

    .d3 {
      border-color: #10b98155;
    }

    .d3 .dnum,
    .d3 .dlabel {
      color: #10b981;
    }

    .d2 {
      border-color: #38bdf855;
    }

    .d2 .dnum,
    .d2 .dlabel {
      color: var(--accent3);
    }

    .d1 {
      border-color: #a855f755;
    }

    .d1 .dnum,
    .d1 .dlabel {
      color: var(--accent2);
    }

    /* ── Code block ── */
    .codeblock {
      background: var(--code-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 22px 26px;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #9090c0;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 800px;
    }

    .codeblock .comment {
      color: #444466;
    }

    .codeblock .cmd {
      color: var(--accent3);
    }

    .codeblock .kw {
      color: var(--accent1);
    }

    .codeblock .str {
      color: #a3e635;
    }

    /* ── Flow diagram ── */
    .flow {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 960px;
      flex-wrap: nowrap;
    }

    .flow-node {
      flex: 1;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 16px 10px;
      text-align: center;
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .flow-node .fn-label {
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    .flow-node .fn-title {
      font-size: 17px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .flow-arrow {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 20px;
      padding: 0 6px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    /* ── Stat chips ── */
    .chips {
      display: flex;
      gap: 14px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .chip {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 30px;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 500;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
    }

    .chip-dot {
      width: 8px;
      height: 8px;
      border-radius: 50%;
    }

    /* ── Roadmap ── */
    .roadmap-item {
      display: flex;
      gap: 18px;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .roadmap-num {
      width: 36px;
      height: 36px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 800;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      margin-top: 2px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent1), var(--accent2));
      color: white;
    }

    .roadmap-item p {
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    /* ── Title slide deco ── */
    .flame-bg {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      pointer-events: none;
      background:
        radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 40% at 50% 100%, rgba(232, 97, 26, 0.18) 0%, transparent 70%),
        radial-gradient(ellipse 40% 30% at 20% 80%, rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.10) 0%, transparent 60%);
    }

    .title-badge {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      background: rgba(232, 97, 26, 0.12);
      border: 1px solid rgba(232, 97, 26, 0.3);
      border-radius: 30px;
      padding: 7px 18px;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--accent1);
      margin-bottom: 28px;
    }

    .headline-mono {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      color: var(--accent1);
    }

    /* ── Nav ── */
    .nav {
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 36px;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 16px;
      z-index: 100;
      background: rgba(19, 19, 30, 0.85);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 40px;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    }

    .nav-btn {
      background: none;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      color: var(--muted);
      width: 32px;
      height: 32px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      border-radius: 50%;
      transition: all 0.2s;
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    .nav-btn:hover {
      background: var(--border);
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .nav-dots {
      display: flex;
      gap: 6px;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .nav-dot {
      width: 6px;
      height: 6px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--border);
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: all 0.2s;
    }

    .nav-dot.active {
      background: var(--accent1);
      width: 20px;
      border-radius: 3px;
    }

    .slide-num {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      min-width: 40px;
      text-align: right;
    }

    /* ── Animated gradient text ── */
    .grad {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent1) 0%, #f59e0b 40%, var(--accent2) 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }

    /* ── Separator line ── */
    .sep {
      width: 48px;
      height: 3px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent1), var(--accent2));
      border-radius: 2px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    /* ── List ── */
    ul.nice {
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    ul.nice li::before {
      content: '→';
      color: var(--accent1);
      margin-right: 10px;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <div class="deck" id="deck">

    <!-- ── 0 · Title ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide active center" id="slide-0">
      <div class="flame-bg"></div>
      <div class="title-badge">🔥 Multi-Agent Debate Engine</div>
      <h1><span class="headline-mono">heated</span><span class="grad">-debate</span></h1>
      <div class="sep" style="margin: 24px auto;"></div>
      <p style="max-width:540px; font-size:clamp(17px,2vw,23px); color:#8888aa;">
        Two LLM agents argue until a great design emerges. An architect proposes. A reviewer challenges.
        A creativity dial cools round by round.
      </p>
      <div class="chips mt40">
        <div class="chip">
          <div class="chip-dot" style="background:var(--accent3)"></div>bun / TypeScript
        </div>
        <div class="chip">
          <div class="chip-dot" style="background:#f59e0b"></div>Claude · Codex
        </div>
        <div class="chip">
          <div class="chip-dot" style="background:var(--accent2)"></div>No API key needed
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 1 · The Idea ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-1">
      <div class="eyebrow">The Idea</div>
      <h2 style="max-width:700px;">Good design emerges from structured disagreement</h2>
      <div class="sep mt28"></div>
      <div class="cols2 mt28" style="max-width:860px;">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🏗️</div>
          <h3>Agent A — Architect</h3>
          <p>Proposes implementation plans. Refines based on feedback. Sends diffs, not full repeats.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🔍</div>
          <h3>Agent B — Reviewer</h3>
          <p>Challenges proposals, finds flaws, identifies edge cases. Forces the plan to earn its shape.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mt28" style="max-width:680px; text-align:center; color:var(--muted);">
        Both agents run in the same model or across models. No shared context — each sees only what the other sends.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 2 · Round Loop ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-2">
      <div class="eyebrow">How a Debate Runs</div>
      <h2 style="max-width:640px; text-align:center;">One topic · N rounds · two voices</h2>
      <div class="mt40 flow">
        <div class="flow-node" style="border-color:#e8611a55;">
          <div class="fn-label" style="color:var(--accent1);">Input</div>
          <div class="fn-title">topic.md</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-node" style="border-color:#f59e0b55;">
          <div class="fn-label" style="color:#f59e0b;">Round 1–N</div>
          <div class="fn-title">Agent A<br><span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">proposes</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-node" style="border-color:#a855f755;">
          <div class="fn-label" style="color:var(--accent2);">Round 1–N</div>
          <div class="fn-title">Agent B<br><span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">reviews</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-node" style="border-color:#38bdf855;">
          <div class="fn-label" style="color:var(--accent3);">Output</div>
          <div class="fn-title">Transcript<br><span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">.md log</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card mt40" style="max-width:840px; border-color:var(--border);">
        <p>B's response always becomes A's next prompt. No moderator — just the ping-pong of proposal and critique, with
          context carried forward via <code>--resume</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cols2 mt28" style="max-width:840px;">
        <div class="agent-box agent-a">
          <div class="agent-label">Agent A · Round 2</div>
          <p style="font-size:15px;">"Addressing the Decimal-from-float issue: switching constructor to
            <code>Decimal(str(price))</code> to prevent float precision drift…"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="agent-box agent-b">
          <div class="agent-label">Agent B · Round 2</div>
          <p style="font-size:15px;">"The <code>allow_short</code> semantics are still underspecified. Does it block the
            trade or clamp position to zero? Edge case: short then long same tick."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 3 · Creativity Dial ───────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide center" id="slide-3">
      <div class="eyebrow">Creativity Dial</div>
      <h2>Temperature by prompt, not by API</h2>
      <p class="mt16" style="max-width:560px; color:var(--muted);">Each round injects a behavioral prefix. The dial
        cools linearly from <strong>Wild → Precise</strong> across rounds.</p>
      <div class="dial-row mt40">
        <div class="dial-step d5">
          <div class="dlabel">Wild</div>
          <div class="dnum">5</div>
          <div class="ddesc">Radical alternatives.<br>Question the premise.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dial-step d4">
          <div class="dlabel">Creative</div>
          <div class="dnum">4</div>
          <div class="ddesc">New ideas.<br>Challenge assumptions.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dial-step d3">
          <div class="dlabel">Balanced</div>
          <div class="dnum">3</div>
          <div class="ddesc">Mix ideas<br>with refinement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dial-step d2">
          <div class="dlabel">Focused</div>
          <div class="dnum">2</div>
          <div class="ddesc">Fix issues.<br>No new directions.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dial-step d1">
          <div class="dlabel">Precise</div>
          <div class="dnum">1</div>
          <div class="ddesc">Converge.<br>Final decisions only.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card mt40" style="max-width:760px; text-align:left;">
        <p>The subscription CLIs don't expose temperature. The dial is the only behavioral modulator — and it's the
          trainable signal for RL later.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 4 · Architecture ──────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-4">
      <div class="eyebrow">Architecture</div>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">shelley.ts — the Bun engine</h2>
      <div class="cols2 mt40" style="max-width:960px; gap:30px; align-items:start;">
        <div class="stack">
          <div class="card" style="border-color:#38bdf855;">
            <h3 style="color:var(--accent3);">🦩 Claude backend</h3>
            <p>Session continuity via <code>--resume &lt;session-id&gt;</code>. New sessions with
              <code>--session-id</code> + <code>--system-prompt</code>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-color:#a855f755;">
            <h3 style="color:var(--accent2);">⚡ Codex backend</h3>
            <p>Stateless calls via <code>codex exec --sandbox read-only</code>. Conversation history windowed manually
              per-agent.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-color:#f59e0b55;">
            <h3 style="color:#f59e0b;">🔐 Env sanitation</h3>
            <p>Strips provider API keys before spawning CLIs. You stay on subscription auth — no accidental billing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stack">
          <div class="codeblock">
            <span class="comment"># Run 5 rounds, default topic</span>
            <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="str">5</span>

            <span class="comment"># Topic from file, 3 rounds</span>
            <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/stock-trades/topic.md <span
              class="str">3</span>

            <span class="comment"># Switch both agents to Codex</span>
            <span class="kw">MODEL_A</span>=codex:gpt-5 <span class="kw">MODEL_B</span>=codex:gpt-5 \
            <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/my-topic/topic.md <span
              class="str">5</span>

            <span class="comment"># Resume a partial run</span>
            <span class="kw">RESUME_FROM_LOG</span>=debates/my-topic/20260227_1930.md \
            <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/my-topic/topic.md <span
              class="str">7</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="font-size:15px;">
            <strong>Context injection</strong><br>
            <p class="mt16">Put a <code>context.txt</code> next to your <code>topic.md</code> listing repo-relative file
              paths. shelley.ts reads them fresh every run — no copies, agents always see current source.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 5 · Debate topic format ────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-5">
      <div class="eyebrow">Running a Debate</div>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Drop a topic file, get a transcript</h2>
      <div class="cols2 mt40" style="max-width:960px; align-items:start;">
        <div class="stack">
          <p
            style="font-size:14px; color:var(--muted); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; font-weight:600;">
            Directory layout</p>
          <div class="codeblock" style="font-size:14px;">
            debates/
            stock-trades/
            topic.md <span class="comment">← 1–3 sentences, no code</span>
            context.txt <span class="comment">← file paths to inject</span>
            20260223_230831.md <span class="comment">← transcript</span>
            review-dials-refactor/
            topic.md
            context.txt
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>topic.md</h3>
            <p style="font-size:15px; margin-top:8px; font-style:italic; color:#8888bb;">"Design a Python function that
              takes a list of stock trades and outputs a portfolio summary with current positions, average cost basis,
              and realized P&amp;L."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stack">
          <p
            style="font-size:14px; color:var(--muted); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; font-weight:600;">
            Transcript output</p>
          <div class="agent-box agent-a" style="margin-bottom:12px;">
            <div class="agent-label">Agent A · sonnet · 38s</div>
            <p style="font-size:15px;">Proposes typed <code>Trade</code> dataclass, separate <code>Position</code>
              accumulator, FIFO lot matching for realized P&amp;L…</p>
          </div>
          <div class="agent-box agent-b">
            <div class="agent-label">Agent B · sonnet · 44s</div>
            <p style="font-size:15px;">Raises: <code>Decimal(price)</code> from float is unsafe. Boundary: what if qty
              is 0? <code>allow_short</code> behavior on same-tick reversal underspecified.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card mt16" style="font-size:15px;">
            Per-round timing + stats table appended to every transcript, with both agent IDs and session UUIDs.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 6 · Multi-model ───────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide center" id="slide-6">
      <div class="eyebrow">Model Support</div>
      <h2>Any two models. Any combination.</h2>
      <div class="sep" style="margin: 24px auto;"></div>
      <div class="cols3 mt28" style="max-width:900px;">
        <div class="card" style="border-color:#38bdf855;">
          <div class="card-icon">☁️</div>
          <h3>Claude (claude:*)</h3>
          <p>Persistent sessions via <code>--resume</code>. haiku, sonnet, opus. No API key — subscription login.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="border-color:#a855f755;">
          <div class="card-icon">⚡</div>
          <h3>Codex (codex:*)</h3>
          <p>Stateless <code>codex exec</code>. History windowed per-agent. Reasoning effort tunable via env var.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="border-color:#10b98155;">
          <div class="card-icon">🌐</div>
          <h3>Any via LiteLLM</h3>
          <p><code>later/pynaille.py</code> routes to Gemini, GPT-4o, and any LiteLLM provider with API keys.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="codeblock mt40" style="max-width:760px; font-size:15px;">
        <span class="comment"># Claude vs Claude</span>
        <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/perf/topic.md <span
          class="str">5</span>

        <span class="comment"># Codex vs Codex, high reasoning</span>
        <span class="kw">MODEL_A</span>=codex <span class="kw">MODEL_B</span>=codex <span
          class="kw">CODEX_REASONING_EFFORT</span>=high \
        <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/perf/topic.md <span
          class="str">5</span>

        <span class="comment"># Mixed: Claude architect vs Codex reviewer</span>
        <span class="kw">MODEL_A</span>=sonnet <span class="kw">MODEL_B</span>=codex <span class="cmd">bun
          shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/perf/topic.md <span class="str">5</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 7 · Roadmap ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-7">
      <div class="eyebrow">What Comes Next</div>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">From debates to design machines</h2>
      <div class="cols2 mt40" style="max-width:960px; align-items:start; gap:20px;">
        <div class="stack" style="gap:16px;">
          <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="roadmap-num">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Dial vector</h3>
              <p>Expand from one scalar to a vector: creativity, risk tolerance, verbosity, deference — per agent, per
                round.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="roadmap-num">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Phase architecture</h3>
              <p>Brainstorm → Hard spec → Scaffold → Tests → Fill-in. Each phase in its own conversation; output feeds
                next.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="roadmap-num">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Tournament + judge</h3>
              <p>Run N parallel debates, different dial settings or model pairings. A judge agent scores output. Winner
                advances.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stack" style="gap:16px;">
          <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="roadmap-num">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3>RL over dial vectors</h3>
              <p>Treat the dial vector as the action space; judge score is reward. Bayesian opt / evolutionary
                strategies — no deep RL infra needed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="roadmap-num">5</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Agent SDK path</h3>
              <p>With an API key, switch to the Claude Agent SDK for persistent in-process agents — eliminates the ~50s
                cold-start per turn.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="roadmap-num">6</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Token accounting</h3>
              <p>Add token counts per turn to transcripts; feed into cost-aware dial optimization.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 8 · Close ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="slide center" id="slide-8">
      <div class="flame-bg"></div>
      <div class="eyebrow">Get Started</div>
      <h1 class="grad">Let them fight.</h1>
      <div class="sep" style="margin: 24px auto;"></div>
      <div class="codeblock mt16" style="max-width:620px; font-size:16px; text-align:left;">
        <span class="comment"># install bun, clone, debate</span>
        <span class="cmd">bun shelley.ts</span> <span class="kw">-f</span> debates/stock-trades/topic.md <span
          class="str">5</span>
      </div>
      <div class="chips mt40">
        <div class="chip">
          <div class="chip-dot" style="background:var(--accent1)"></div>github.com/vd1/heated-debate
        </div>
        <div class="chip">
          <div class="chip-dot" style="background:var(--accent3)"></div>shelley.ts · bun
        </div>
        <div class="chip">
          <div class="chip-dot" style="background:var(--accent2)"></div>No API key needed
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /deck -->

  <!-- ── Nav ── -->
  <nav class="nav" id="nav">
    <button class="nav-btn" id="prev-btn" onclick="go(-1)" title="Previous">←</button>
    <div class="nav-dots" id="dots"></div>
    <button class="nav-btn" id="next-btn" onclick="go(1)" title="Next">→</button>
    <span class="slide-num" id="slide-num">1 / 9</span>
  </nav>

  <script>
    const slides = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.slide'));
    const dotsEl = document.getElementById('dots');
    const numEl = document.getElementById('slide-num');
    let cur = 0;

    // Build dots
    slides.forEach((_, i) => {
      const d = document.createElement('div');
      d.className = 'nav-dot' + (i === 0 ? ' active' : '');
      d.onclick = () => goTo(i);
      dotsEl.appendChild(d);
    });

    function goTo(n) {
      if (n === cur) return;
      const prev = slides[cur];
      prev.classList.remove('active');
      prev.classList.add('exit');
      setTimeout(() => prev.classList.remove('exit'), 300);
      cur = (n + slides.length) % slides.length;
      slides[cur].classList.add('active');
      document.querySelectorAll('.nav-dot').forEach((d, i) => d.classList.toggle('active', i === cur));
      numEl.textContent = `${cur + 1} / ${slides.length}`;
    }

    function go(dir) { goTo(cur + dir); }

    document.addEventListener('keydown', e => {
      if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'ArrowDown' || e.key === ' ') { e.preventDefault(); go(1); }
      if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' || e.key === 'ArrowUp') { e.preventDefault(); go(-1); }
    });

    // Swipe on mobile
    let sx = null;
    document.addEventListener('touchstart', e => { sx = e.touches[0].clientX; });
    document.addEventListener('touchend', e => {
      if (sx === null) return;
      const dx = e.changedTouches[0].clientX - sx;
      if (Math.abs(dx) > 50) go(dx < 0 ? 1 : -1);
      sx = null;
    });
  </script>
</body>

</html>

--- README.md ---
# heated-debate

Multi-agent debate engine that pits LLM agents against each other in structured, round-based design reviews. An architect proposes, a reviewer critiques, and a creativity dial cools from wild to precise across rounds.

## Quick start

```bash
# TypeScript frontend (bun + CLI backends; supports claude/codex CLI subscription login)
bun shelley.ts 5                                          # 5 rounds, default topic
bun shelley.ts -f debates/stock-trades/topic.md 3         # 3 rounds, file topic
MODEL_A=codex:gpt-5 MODEL_B=codex:gpt-5 bun shelley.ts -f debates/stock-trades/topic.md 3

# Python frontend (uses LiteLLM — needs API keys in .env)
uv run later/pynaille.py --rounds 5 --topic "Design a cache"
uv run later/pynaille.py --agent-a gemini/gemini-2.5-flash --agent-b gemini/gemini-2.5-flash
```

## Files

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `shelley.ts` | Bun frontend — orchestrates debates via CLI backends. Supports `claude:*` and `codex:*` model specs (via CLI subscriptions, not API keys). |
| `later/pynaille.py` | Python frontend — orchestrates debates via LiteLLM. Supports any model LiteLLM can route to. Outputs JSON logs. |
| `later/dials.py` | Shared creativity dial + temperature schedule. Importable as a Python module and callable as a CLI. Maps round number to a creativity level (5→1) and temperature (1.0→0.3). |
| `later/streamy.py` | Test harness for `claude -p --output-format stream-json`. Exploratory — not used in debates yet. |
| `pyproject.toml` | Python project config. Dependencies: `litellm`, `python-dotenv`. |
| `debate.md` | Protocol doc for agent-to-agent code review via GitHub issues. |
| `notes/what-comes-next.md` | Roadmap: stream-json mode, phase architecture, tournament + judge, RL over dial vectors. |
| `notes/review-notes.md` | Review notes on the project's docs and early debate logs. |
## Debate topics

Each topic lives in its own directory under `debates/`:

```
debates/
  stock-trades/
    topic.md              ← what we're debating (1-3 sentences)
    20260223_230831.md    ← timestamped transcript
    20260223_pynaille.md
  review-dials-refactor/
    topic.md
    context.txt           ← file paths for agents to review
```

- **`topic.md`** — a short description of the debate topic. No code, no instructions.
- **`context.txt`** — optional list of file paths (relative to repo root, one per line). shelley.ts reads the actual files and includes them in the agents' first-round prompts. No copies — agents always see current source.
- **Transcripts** — timestamped markdown logs written after each run.

## Creativity dial

The dial cools linearly from 5 (Wild) to 1 (Precise) across rounds. Each level prepends a behavioral instruction to the agent's prompt:

| Dial | Label | Instruction |
|------|-------|-------------|
| 5 | Wild | Explore radical alternatives. Question the premise. |
| 4 | Creative | Suggest improvements. Challenge assumptions. |
| 3 | Balanced | Mix new ideas with refinement. Weigh tradeoffs. |
| 2 | Focused | Refine the current approach. Fix issues. No new directions. |
| 1 | Precise | Converge. Correctness, consistency, completeness only. |

In later/pynaille.py, the API temperature also cools (1.0→0.3). In shelley.ts, the dial prefix is the only behavioral modulator (claude/codex CLI doesn't expose temperature).

## Environment

- Python ≥3.12, managed with `uv`
- TypeScript frontend requires `bun`; bun auto-loads `.env`, so shelley.ts strips provider API keys when spawning `claude`/`codex` CLIs to stay on subscription auth
- Python frontend requires a `.env` with API keys for your chosen LiteLLM provider


--- notes/what-comes-next.md ---
# What comes next

## 1. Soft temperature via prompt dials
Replace real temperature (API-only) with prompt-injected behavioral knobs.
Start with a single scalar (creativity 1-5), test whether claude -p
output meaningfully shifts between dial settings. Then expand to a vector:
- Creativity: 1-5
- Risk tolerance: 1-5
- Verbosity: 1-5
- Deference: 1-5

Embed the dial in each exchange so it can vary per round per agent.
This is the trainable signal for RL later.

## 2. Stream JSON mode
~~Test `claude -p --input-format stream-json --output-format stream-json`
to keep a single process alive via stdin/stdout.~~ **Tested — doesn't work
that way.** `--input-format stream-json` is for piping one process's output
into another (`claude ... | claude --input-format stream-json`), not for
interactive multi-turn on a single process. Multi-turn still requires
`--resume` with separate invocations.

What *does* work: `--output-format json` gives structured results (session
ID, token counts, result text) instead of raw text. A Python orchestrator
using `--resume` + JSON output is the realistic subscription-path upgrade
over shelley.sh — same per-turn spawning, but with proper structured parsing
and asyncio concurrency.

For true single-process persistent agents, need the Agent SDK
(`claude-agent-sdk`) which requires an API key (not subscription).

## 3. Phase architecture
Split the debate into sequential phases, each its own conversation:

1. **Brainstorm** — high creativity dial, divergent exploration
2. **Hard spec** — low creativity, converge on precise plan
3. **Scaffold** — lay out files, interfaces, types from the spec
4. **Test** — write tests against the spec before implementation
5. **Fill in** — implement with continuous review per chunk

Output of each phase feeds as context to the next.

## 4. Tournament + judge
Run N parallel conversations (same phase, different dial settings or
model pairings). A judge agent (or panel of 3) scores the outputs.
Winner advances to next phase.

## 5. RL (or bayesian opt) over dial vectors
Treat the dial vector (per agent, per round, per phase) as the action
space. Judge score is the reward. Low-dimensional optimization —
Bayesian opt or evolutionary strategies, not deep RL.


## 6. Variations

add tokens to players moves in log
should we let agents digress from the topic?
exchange tips between agents -> write to agent's memory
interet user (≠ interet benchmark) -> on comprend mieux ses besoins et les difficultés

## 7. Streamy: Python orchestrator (subscription path)

Replace shelley.sh with a Python asyncio orchestrator (`streamy.py`) that:
- Spawns `claude -p --output-format json --resume <session>` per turn
- Parses structured JSON for session IDs, token usage, results
- Manages two agent sessions via `--resume` + `--session-id`
- Runs concurrently where possible (e.g. both agents' tool init)
- Logs to markdown like shelley, but with token counts per turn
- Integrates dials.py via `--append-system-prompt`

Still one process per turn (unavoidable on subscription), but structured
output + Python control flow > bash string wrangling.

## 8. Agent SDK path (API key path)

For true efficiency gains, the Claude Agent SDK (`pip install claude-agent-sdk`)
gives persistent in-process agents with no per-turn spawning overhead:
- `query()` returns async iterator of typed messages
- Session continuity via `resume=session_id`
- Hooks for pre/post tool use, permissions callbacks
- Custom subagents with focused tool access
- Structured output via `--json-schema`

Trade-off: requires `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (API billing), not subscription.
But eliminates the ~50s cold-start per turn and gives native Python control
over the agent loop. Worth exploring once the debate protocol stabilizes.



